Title: A Beautiful Mind
Summary: Won a bunch of Oscars and is about maths I think.

Summary: John Krasinski's directorial debut with an excellent performance by Emily Blunt which won her well-deserved SAG Award. This movie is an incredible scary movie that completely teleports you into a dystopian world where any sound can kill you. So not great for Hanney.

Title: A Simple Favor
Summary: You don't quite know where this movie is heading but its mystery, Anna Kendrick and Blake Lively's unlikely chemistry and Henry Golding make this a fun watch and I'm curious what's gonna happen in part 2.

Title: Aladdin
Summary: Speechless is the central piece of this movie. The epicness of Naomi Scott's voice and Paul & Pasek's genius makes this song unforgettable. Will Smith is blue (as always) and Aladdin is hot (as always).

Title: Aladin
Summary: We don't know the origin of this masterpiece of an Iranian knock-off but it is hilarious to have in the collection.

Title: Alf [Season 1]
Summary: I've watched one episode and didn't like it. I'm sure it had it's time and was funny at some point but it's just not my cup of tea.

Title: Allegiant
Summary: Oh Allegiant. What a crazy downfall of what otherwise seemed to be a promising setup for a good teenage science fiction franchise. Allegiant is a waste of time and one of the regrets in this collection, but it has to be in there it completes the franchise.

Title: Angels & Demons
Summary: I am surprised that I don't watch this movie more often and I always forget that Ewan McGregor is in it. It's a great scavenger hunt throughout beautiful Rome and gets you on the edge of your seat every time.

Title: Annihilation
Summary: One of the first Netflix productions released on Netflix I remember seeing. A great film with women at the center and beautiful VFX transporting you and leaving you in awe. Of course it's Alex Garland's genius.

Title: Aquaman
Summary: One of the good DC films in the era of Wonder Woman. The VFX look super cool with the hair underwater. Could be shorter though.

Title: Argo
Summary: Controversial, but I really liked this movie. I am a sucker for credits where they compare the real people with the actors. But also it's an exciting movie and well-made so leave me alone, or should I say "Argo f*** yourself".

Title: Arrival
Summary: A masterpiece. Linguistics and Aliens are an unlikely combination but it all makes sense and this movie has a twist that will forever leave me with my jaw on the floor just like the first time I saw it. Villeneuve, Adams, Renner. What else do you want? Kangaroo ðŸ¤·
